-- Wilbur Ross to seek up to $2 bln for private equity fund -Bloomberg
-- 
-- Tue Oct 14, 2014 07:47PM EDT
-- None



Oct 14 (Reuters) - WL Ross & Co, run by U.S. billionaire Wilbur Ross, is seeking as much as $2 billion for its next private equity fund, Bloomberg reported on Tuesday.

The company is targeting between $1 billion to $2 billion, Bloomberg said, citing two people familiar with the matter. (http://bloom.bg/1o9x9ca) The $1 billion to $2 billion WL Ross will seek does not include separate accounts or side-by-side capital, Bloomberg reporting, citing one of the people. A unit of asset manager Invesco Ltd <IVZ.N>, WL Ross & Co invests in and restructures financially distressed companies focusing on energy, financial services, health care, heavy materials and transportation sectors.